<br>
Ok, you asked for it.<br>
<br>
1.  I was under the impression that there was a representative from each guild in the SGA council.  This representative was to vote on matters concerning inviting new guilds.  I don't see how hard this is ?  There are only 4 guilds now, that's four representatives.  Who's abstaining ?  Who hasn't voted ?<br>
<br>
2.  The only guilds that I have seen post on our message board for membership are VC and IA.  They're the only guilds that I know of that have also joined us on raids.  I think there needs to be set dates posted that other guilds can see as to when we will be inviting others.  The way it sits now, VC and IA and whoever else applies has no timeframe.  To be honest, they've been more than patient now, as it has appeared that we have been ignoring them.  I'd like to see 2 guilds or 1 guild every 2 months.  Have a section where new guilds apply.  Our representatives vote on them, if there are 7 guilds in the queue, then they vote on the 7 guilds, giving them a value of 1-7, where 7 is the guild they want in the most.  You total up everyone's points, and the two guilds with the most points gets invited.  Two months later, we do the same thing.  This time the guilds that were on the waiting list start with a preset 5 points, and we do the process over again.  If for some reason 50% of the representatives deem that a guild should not be invited, then they should be informed of such immediately, and removed from the voting.  <br>
<br>
3.  I hear people saying that &quot;we're big enough&quot;.  When do we stop inviting people ?  My response to that is, why ?  The SGA is an alliance, it's not one big guild.  So what if we have 10 guilds in it ?  The WHOLE PREMISE behind the SGA was to allow smaller guilds accomplish things that they COULD NOT accomplish on their own.  It wasn't designed to be just big enough to do stuff on it's own.<br>
<br>
If the SGA is to become only so big then stop allowing other guilds to join, then the SGA has become exactly what I have attempted to avoid.  It will be no better than a larger guild that descriminates against classes and levels and size.  We'll be doing raids and not inviting friends.<br>
<br>
4.  People say we're inviting guilds too fast.  That they haven't gotten to know everyone else yet.  Do you know everyone in your own guild ?  I don't.  Does this stop me from treating them as friends when I see them ?  No.  Does this mean Amnesty is too big ?  No.  Have I met and made friends with a lot of new people because of SGA ?  Yes.  <br>
<br>
5.  Diadem will be getting his Epic here shortly.  I plan on setting up a raid to take out the General for this weekend.  That will push the total of Epics to two.  That's two more than I ever thought we would have by now.  Is there anyone else that thought the SGA would be so close to taking out VS or Trak at this point ?<br>
<br>
6.  Word has it that Hareq doesn't attend any raids that he doesn't lead.  Is this true ?  I think not.  Did I not go to Kael and help Malleolus ?  How about when I helped Holt on his KK raid ?  Zenknight's raid in Kithicor Forrest ?<br>
<br>
I think you're misinterpretting my intent.  The problem is if I attend a raid, then people expect me to lead it.  I don't want to lead every raid.  I want others to lead them as well.<br>
<br>
I forsee a time when Zenknight is leading a raid into Hate, and I'm helping lead several groups into Velks. Lab.  Across the world Boofa is leading a group to take out the Black Reavers.<br>
<br>
So far Krytog, Zenknight and Lingling have stepped up big time, and have led some very successful raids.  I applaud them on their hard work.  It is very difficult to lead a raid, and if you haven't tried, I suggest you do. <p>Hareq Ghoulslayer, 54 Paladin<br>
Amnesty</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FFFF00>- </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bsaryrnguildallianceboard>saryrnguildallianceboard</a><font color=#FFFF00> - </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1>General Discussion</a> <font color=#FFFF00> - </font><br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href=http://www.entercasino.com/main.cgi?refererID=502600>What's your game? Casino On Net</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><IMG SRC="http://service.bfast.com/bfast/serve?bfmid=7279965&siteid=33932331&bfpage=expertc_tax" BORDER="0" WIDTH="1" HEIGHT="1" NOSAVE >
